registers.name: Stream_Switch_Adaptive_Clock_Gate_Status
registers.description: Status of Stream Switch Adaptive Clock Gate

bit_fields.name: Active
bit_fields.description: 1=adaptive clock gating is active, feature enabled and switch idle for time-out, switch data path is not being clocked; 0=adaptive clock gating is not active (feature may be enabled or disabled). (Non-latching status register)

registers.name: Stream_Switch_Adaptive_Clock_Gate_Abort_Period
registers.description: Status of Stream Switch Adaptive Clock Gate Abort Period

bit_fields.name: Abort_Period
bit_fields.description: Abort Period for adaptive clock gate, defined as 2^N. Supported range for field: [3-12]. Giving periods: [8,16,32,.,4096] cycles. Default period: 128 cycles. If Stream_Switch_Adaptive_Clock_Gate is disabled, this field has no effect.Currently, only officially supported period is 128 cycles.

bit_fields.name: DMA_Adaptive_Clock_Gate
bit_fields.description: Enable adaptive clock gate in DMA when it is idle

bit_fields.name: Stream_Switch_Adaptive_Clock_Gate
bit_fields.description: Enable adaptive clock gate in stream switch when it has been idle for X cycles

bit_fields.name: CTE_Clock_Enable
bit_fields.description: Enable the clock to Event, Trace

bit_fields.name: PL_Interface_Clock_Enable
bit_fields.description: Enable the clock to PL interface

bit_fields.name: Stream_Switch_Clock_Enable
bit_fields.description: Enable the clock to stream switch, ctrl-pkt handler

bit_fields.name: NoC_Module_Clock_Enable
bit_fields.description: Enable the clock to NoC Module

bit_fields.name: NoC_Module_Reset
bit_fields.description: Reset the NoC Module

registers.name: Column_Clock_Control
registers.description: Control of global clock gating (privileged) (TMR protection)

bit_fields.name: Clock_Buffer_Enable
bit_fields.description: Column clock gate: Control the global clock buffer, affects all tiles above (Tile & MEM). This Shim tile unaffected. 1=Clock enabled; 0=Clock gated

registers.name: AIE_Tile_Column_Reset
registers.description: Reset for all ME tiles in the column above (privileged) (TMR protection)

bit_fields.name: Reset
bit_fields.description: 1=Reset all AIE tiles in the column above
